Class DefaultMultiVariableConstraint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.grinder.core.AbstractExpression
      • com.sri.ai.expresso.helper.AbstractExpressionWrapper
        • com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.core.constraint.AbstractConstraint
          • com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.core.constraint.DefaultMultiVariableConstraint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Expression, Constraint, Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<Object>

    public class DefaultMultiVariableConstraint
extends AbstractConstraint
    An Constraint on multiple variables. Unlike MultiVariableContextWithCheckedProperty and its extension CompleteMultiVariableContext, it does not check for satisfiability or any other property, but simply keeps an aggregate of single-variable constraints.
    Author:
    braz

      • conjoin

        public Constraint conjoin(Expression formula,
                          Context context)
        Description copied from interface: Constraint
        Returns an SGDPLLTTester representing the conjunction of this constraint and a given formula, or null if they are contradictory.

        At this point, the formula should be either a literal, or a Constraint.

        Extensions may want to override this method if there are more efficient ways of conjoining with (certain types of) constraints than simply treating them as a formula

        Parameters:
        formula - the formula to be conjoined.
        context - the context
        Returns:
        the application result or null if contradiction.
